livekit-wakeword bundles the openWakeWord frozen audio frontend
(melspectrogram.onnx + Google speech embedding model).

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
openWakeWord pretrained classifiers
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The built-in wake word models (alexa, hey_jarvis, hey_mycroft, hey_rhasspy)
are from the openWakeWord project:

  https://github.com/dscripka/openWakeWord

  Copyright 2023 David Scripka

  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0

Model release assets are downloaded from
https://github.com/dscripka/openWakeWord/releases/tag/v0.5.1
at first boot and stored in /data/models.

The hey_livekit model is from the livekit-wakeword repository and is
licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (see above).
